</ul>

<h2 id="latex-templates">LaTex templates</h2>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://journals.aas.org/aastex-package-for-manuscript-preparation/">AASTeX</a>: templates for ApJ, ApJL and ApJS. Note that ApJL has a limitation for the number of figures. Check the overleaf version here: <a href="https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/aastex-template-for-submissions-to-the-astrophysical-journal/bpkjwktvsqwp">AASTeX Template for submissions to AAS Journals </a>. Personally I prefer AAS templates than MNRAS one.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/monthly-notices-of-the-royal-astronomical-society-mnras-latex-template-and-guide-for-authors/kqnjzrwjwjth">MNRAS</a>: template for MNRAS. Alexie likes this template.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Curriculum Vitae: I recommend this <a href="https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/cv-for-freshers/jkpwvnrdrxpm">template</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Template for book: I highly recommend <a href="https://www.overleaf.com/latex/templates/the-legrand-orange-book-template-english/jtctyfmnpppc">Legrand Orange Book Template</a>. I wrote a book using this template for the astronomy olympiad training last year.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>For Chinese templates, check <a href="http://www.latexstudio.net">LaTex开源小屋</a>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>LaTeX is also very convenient for taking notes on physics classes. Check my notes on Statistical Physics <a href="https://astrojacobli.github.io/Docs/LaTeX/NotesTemplate.zip">here</a>. (You can compile the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.tex</code> file succesfully by putting <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.tex</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">.png</code> in the same folder.)</p>
  </li>
</ul>

